\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {A.1}{\ignorespaces Adopted physical and observational properties of the target protostellar systems. The table lists the stellar and disk masses, central (stellar + disk) mass used in the modeling, systemic velocity, disk inclination and position angle reported in the literature, as well as the bolometric temperature ($T_{\rm  bol}$) used as an evolutionary indicator. These parameters are taken from previous observational studies and are used either as fixed inputs, reference values for comparison, or auxiliary information in the streamer modeling analysis. The inclination angle with i=0 corresponds to a face-on disk.}}{51}{table.caption.39}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:observations}{{A.1}{51}{Adopted physical and observational properties of the target protostellar systems. The table lists the stellar and disk masses, central (stellar + disk) mass used in the modeling, systemic velocity, disk inclination and position angle reported in the literature, as well as the bolometric temperature ($T_{\rm bol}$) used as an evolutionary indicator. These parameters are taken from previous observational studies and are used either as fixed inputs, reference values for comparison, or auxiliary information in the streamer modeling analysis. The inclination angle with i=0 corresponds to a face-on disk}{table.caption.39}{}}
